description: Due to the fact that hackers regularly use social engineering sites as a source of information I have intentionally left off many details about the equipment, advisory, training and Information Assurance duties I perform on a daily basis. Acquisition, production and dissemination of commercial satellite imagery including data from WorldView-2, Spot-5, and 6, RapidEye 1-5, RadarSat-2, TerraSar-X and Tandem-X. Support Global disaster recovery operations by providing value added satellite imagery data to various International, US Federal, State and Civil authorities. Operate and perform minor maintenance duties to a mobile ground station capable of acquiring commercial satellite imagery. Perform system administration functions to imagery production system. Software packages and administered in the system include ArcGIS Desktop with several extensions, ERDAS Imagine, RemoteView, PhotoShop CS6, Windows-7 (FIPS compliant and USAF STIG’s applied), Windows Sever 2008R2 (FIPS compliant and USAF STIG’s applied), FalconView, GeoExpress, and many other COTS and GOTS imagery tools. Implement corrective measures as related to scan findings. Perform advisory as well as program management functions to our program. Give briefings or write reports about our program and/or daily activities to commanders, general officers or SES equivalents.
